  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-0096136f-7fff-3ded-3060-26526a37ab30\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed upper ground floor roof terrace area at the rear of the property, by reason of its intended use and siting/location, would adversely impact on neighbour amenities by virtue of privacy intrusion.&nbsp; The proposal is therefore contrary to policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) of the The London Plan (2021), and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009) and the National Planning Policy Framework (as amended) (2019).</span></span><br></p>",
    "<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding: 0pt 5.4pt;\">The proposed works to the front of the property together with upper ground floor roof terrace, by reason of their siting, position and detailed design would result in an obtrusive and incompatible form of development which would fail to respect the character and appearance of the subject locally listed property and the surrounding streetscape and would fail to preserve or enhance the character and appearance of the Graham Road &amp; Mapledene Conservation Area, contrary to policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) and&nbsp; HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of The London Plan (2021), policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) and LP4 (Non-designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD 2009 and the National Planning Policy Framework (2019).</p>"
